The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                                        
	Mohali: Concerned about the growing injuries among Indian players, the BCCI has hired Amit Shah, who worked as KKR physio during IPL III, as the second physio of the national team. The team already have Nitin Patel as their physio, but in the wake of injuries, Patel is finding it difficult to singularly attend to individuals with injuries, as well as the others in general.         
	Mumbai: The problems plaguing the Kochi IPL franchise showed no sign of coming to an end on Monday, with a question mark over Thursdays meeting by Shashi Tharoor. I dont think anyone is going to be there at the meeting. Unless a common ground is reached whats the point in holding a meeting, said Satyajitsinh Gaikwad, the CEO of the consortium.         
	London: Englands cricketers are set to sign their central contracts after the England and Wales Cricket Board reached an agreement with the players union over revisions to the deals.         
	Calcutta: Zimbabwes national cricket team, led by Elton Chigumbura, arrived in South Africa, on Monday, for a short tour of South Africa that includes two Standard Bank InternationalT20 matches, and three MTN one dayers. Ryan McLaren will replace Albie Morkel in the Proteas T20 squad for the two international matches against Zimbabwe.        
	Calcutta: CAB Green scored 251 at the loss of 3 wickets in 63 overs in a rain-affected match against CAB Blue, in SK Acharya Memorial Challenger Trophy, on Monday. Arindam Das hit 123 while Arindam Ghosh made an unbeaten 86 for Green, in a match reduced to 75 overs.         
	Calcutta: Top seed Manoj Sewa beat unseeded Prem Singh 6-3, 2-6, 6-0 in the first round of the Calcutta Hard Court Tennis Championship.         
	Bangalore: Indian shuttler Ajay Jayaram won his second international title after emerging victorious in the Yonex Czech International tournament held in Brno. Jayaram beat Scott Evans of Ireland 21-11, 21-8 in the final.         
	London: Manchester City midfielder Nigel De Jong has been dropped from the Holland squad for the upcoming Euro 2012 qualifiers against Moldova and Sweden, as a punishment for his tackle which broke Hatem Ben Arfas leg on Sunday.         
	Zurich: Fifa said in a statement, Monday that its Emergency Committee has suspended the Nigerian Football Federation (NFF) with immediate effect, due to government interference.     
